cscie97.asn4.housemate.entitlement

Interface IEntitlementServiceAPI

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    EntitlementServiceAPI

    public interface IEntitlementServiceAPI
    Public interface for the EntitlemntServiceAPI. Administrators may use the methods here to create and administer new Roles, Permissions, Resources, and Users, and also define the properties on each. Also contains methods for logging in and logging out, which enable registered users to call restricted interface methods on the IEntitlementServiceAPI, IHouseMateModelServiceAPI, and cscie97.asn4.housemate.controller.IHouseMateControllerServiceAPI classes.

      • canAccess

        boolean canAccess(java.lang.String tokenID,
                java.lang.String permissionID)
        Checks if the User that owns the AccessToken corresponding to the passed tokenID has permission to use the Permission. Looks up the AccessToken's owning User, and inspects their Entitlements to confirm whether or not the user has the corresponding Permission.
        Parameters:
        tokenID - the id of the AccessToken to check
        permissionID - the id of the Permission to check the user for
        Returns:
        true if the user has the Permission, false otherwise
